SIMPLE: theocrasy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Theocrasy
<hw>The*oc"ra*sy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ union of
the soul with God; <?/ God + <?/ a mixing, akin to <?/ to mix.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A mixture of the worship of different gods, as of
Jehovah and idols.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This syncretistic <qex>theocracy</qex> by no means excludes in him
[Solomon] the proper service of idols.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Murphy.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Philos.)</fld> <def>An intimate union of the soul
with God in contemplation, -- an ideal of the Neoplatonists and of some
Oriental mystics.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Theocrat</ent>⟦br⟧
